{
  "interview_id": 202,
  "recommendation_id": null,
  "recommendation_text": "The federal minimum wage should be raised to $30 per hour.",
  "total_segments_available": 96,
  "segments": [
    {
      "segment_id": 1403,
      "audio_id": 8059,
      "text": "Sure, I grew up in New York and it was very interesting.",
      "duration": 5.0,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 5.0,
      "sequence_number": 1,
      "question_id": 5050,
      "global_question_id": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1404,
      "audio_id": 8059,
      "text": "It was a lot of fun.",
      "duration": 1.8399996757507324,
      "start_time": 5.380000114440918,
      "end_time": 7.21999979019165,
      "sequence_number": 2,
      "question_id": 5050,
      "global_question_id": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1405,
      "audio_id": 8059,
      "text": "There was lots to do, lots of culture, lots of diversity, and I enjoyed it quite a bit.",
      "duration": 7.200000286102295,
      "start_time": 7.21999979019165,
      "end_time": 14.420000076293945,
      "sequence_number": 3,
      "question_id": 5050,
      "global_question_id": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1406,
      "audio_id": 8059,
      "text": "My neighborhood was full of people from very diverse backgrounds, and so my friends were also from diverse backgrounds, and I really enjoyed myself growing up.",
      "duration": 13.139999389648438,
      "start_time": 14.420000076293945,
      "end_time": 27.559999465942383,
      "sequence_number": 4,
      "question_id": 5050,
      "global_question_id": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1407,
      "audio_id": 8059,
      "text": "For more information, visit www.fema.",
      "duration": 2.0,
      "start_time": 30.0,
      "end_time": 32.0,
      "sequence_number": 5,
      "question_id": 5050,
      "global_question_id": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1408,
      "audio_id": 8069,
      "text": "Sure, a person who has made a big impact on me would be my father, who is now deceased, but certainly he was a good role model, worked very hard to look after me and the rest of the family.",
      "duration": 17.559999465942383,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 17.559999465942383,
      "sequence_number": 1,
      "question_id": 5072,
      "global_question_id": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1409,
      "audio_id": 8069,
      "text": "And the relationship I had with him, obviously, is I'm his son.",
      "duration": 3.440000534057617,
      "start_time": 17.559999465942383,
      "end_time": 21.0,
      "sequence_number": 2,
      "question_id": 5072,
      "global_question_id": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1410,
      "audio_id": 8069,
      "text": "And we met because I was born, and they meant a lot to me, or he meant a lot to me.",
      "duration": 7.280000686645508,
      "start_time": 21.0,
      "end_time": 28.280000686645508,
      "sequence_number": 3,
      "question_id": 5072,
      "global_question_id": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1411,
      "audio_id": 8069,
      "text": "But as I mentioned, he's now deceased.",
      "duration": 1.7999992370605469,
      "start_time": 28.280000686645508,
      "end_time": 30.079999923706055,
      "sequence_number": 4,
      "question_id": 5072,
      "global_question_id": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1412,
      "audio_id": 8090,
      "text": "Sure.",
      "duration": 9.199999809265137,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 9.199999809265137,
      "sequence_number": 1,
      "question_id": 5080,
      "global_question_id": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1413,
      "audio_id": 8090,
      "text": "Well, the work I do now involves just looking after networks and doing maintenance and troubleshooting and responding to varying issues, you know, communicating with people, and with regards to setting up appointments to look after some of the issues that they're having, if any.",
      "duration": 8.960000038146973,
      "start_time": 9.199999809265137,
      "end_time": 18.15999984741211,
      "sequence_number": 2,
      "question_id": 5080,
      "global_question_id": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1414,
      "audio_id": 8090,
      "text": "And, you know, it's fairly repetitive in some ways, and then, you know, but there's something new each day, so I do get to learn quite a bit over time, and I find it challenging, but I think it's very beneficial for me in order, you know, to properly improve my skill set.",
      "duration": 43.60000038146973,
      "start_time": 19.920000076293945,
      "end_time": 63.52000045776367,
      "sequence_number": 3,
      "question_id": 5080,
      "global_question_id": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1415,
      "audio_id": 8106,
      "text": "Well, sure, sometimes the deadlines to get things done are unrealistic.",
      "duration": 5.800000190734863,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 5.800000190734863,
      "sequence_number": 1,
      "question_id": 5090,
      "global_question_id": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1416,
      "audio_id": 8106,
      "text": "I feel that the people who set up the deadlines don't have a true sense of what it takes to get specific tasks done.",
      "duration": 11.75999927520752,
      "start_time": 5.800000190734863,
      "end_time": 17.559999465942383,
      "sequence_number": 2,
      "question_id": 5090,
      "global_question_id": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1417,
      "audio_id": 8106,
      "text": "And since they don't have that insight, they think that it takes much less time, but it often takes more.",
      "duration": 9.280000686645508,
      "start_time": 17.559999465942383,
      "end_time": 26.84000015258789,
      "sequence_number": 3,
      "question_id": 5090,
      "global_question_id": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1418,
      "audio_id": 8106,
      "text": "And then there's always some issue that pops up, some unforeseen issue that delays things even more.",
      "duration": 9.119998931884766,
      "start_time": 26.84000015258789,
      "end_time": 35.959999084472656,
      "sequence_number": 4,
      "question_id": 5090,
      "global_question_id": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1419,
      "audio_id": 8106,
      "text": "So I think a bit more, I guess, better communication and a better acknowledgment that if the people dealing with the issues are more familiar with the issues, and so that the estimated time to get the issues resolved are going to be more realistic than someone who is not familiar with what's required to get the work done.",
      "duration": 41.840003967285156,
      "start_time": 35.959999084472656,
      "end_time": 77.80000305175781,
      "sequence_number": 5,
      "question_id": 5090,
      "global_question_id": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1420,
      "audio_id": 8106,
      "text": "So I think that, I guess, more discretion with regards to setting the timeline for things.",
      "duration": 10.239997863769531,
      "start_time": 77.80000305175781,
      "end_time": 88.04000091552734,
      "sequence_number": 6,
      "question_id": 5090,
      "global_question_id": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1421,
      "audio_id": 8148,
      "text": "Well, it would affect quite a few people positively.",
      "duration": 3.8399999141693115,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 3.8399999141693115,
      "sequence_number": 1,
      "question_id": 5096,
      "global_question_id": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1422,
      "audio_id": 8148,
      "text": "It wouldn't affect me because I make more than the minimum wage, so I don't work for an hourly wage.",
      "duration": 9.160000085830688,
      "start_time": 3.8399999141693115,
      "end_time": 13.0,
      "sequence_number": 2,
      "question_id": 5096,
      "global_question_id": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1423,
      "audio_id": 8148,
      "text": "I work for, I'm a salaried employee.",
      "duration": 2.880000114440918,
      "start_time": 13.0,
      "end_time": 15.880000114440918,
      "sequence_number": 3,
      "question_id": 5096,
      "global_question_id": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1424,
      "audio_id": 8148,
      "text": "However, people close to me who do work, you know, for the minimum wage, for example, my niece who is saving up for her education, et cetera, I would help her greatly so that she can meet her goals and achieve her, you know, her goals that, you know, getting a degree and a career, et cetera.",
      "duration": 23.960000038146973,
      "start_time": 15.880000114440918,
      "end_time": 39.84000015258789,
      "sequence_number": 4,
      "question_id": 5096,
      "global_question_id": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1425,
      "audio_id": 8148,
      "text": "And with a lot of people, you know, who are employed and struggling because the cost of living has really gone up, especially recently, so the minimum wage has to reflect that.",
      "duration": 15.959999084472656,
      "start_time": 39.84000015258789,
      "end_time": 55.79999923706055,
      "sequence_number": 5,
      "question_id": 5096,
      "global_question_id": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1426,
      "audio_id": 8148,
      "text": "And if it doesn't, then people get very depressed and some people spiral into all kinds of psychological issues or issues with addiction.",
      "duration": 12.39999771118164,
      "start_time": 55.79999923706055,
      "end_time": 68.19999694824219,
      "sequence_number": 6,
      "question_id": 5096,
      "global_question_id": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1427,
      "audio_id": 8148,
      "text": "So it can create other societal problems.",
      "duration": 5.160003662109375,
      "start_time": 68.19999694824219,
      "end_time": 73.36000061035156,
      "sequence_number": 7,
      "question_id": 5096,
      "global_question_id": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1428,
      "audio_id": 8148,
      "text": "That's why the minimum wage is so important, because people who are working need to be able to survive based on the wage they get.",
      "duration": 9.400001525878906,
      "start_time": 73.36000061035156,
      "end_time": 82.76000213623047,
      "sequence_number": 8,
      "question_id": 5096,
      "global_question_id": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1429,
      "audio_id": 8148,
      "text": "And if that's too low, then, you know, regardless of how they how hard they work, you know, they're always going to be, you know, miserable and struggling.",
      "duration": 9.839996337890625,
      "start_time": 82.76000213623047,
      "end_time": 92.5999984741211,
      "sequence_number": 9,
      "question_id": 5096,
      "global_question_id": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1430,
      "audio_id": 8179,
      "text": "Okay, so, you know, I would have to, it would depend on, you know, what someone's expenses are.",
      "duration": 9.0,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 9.0,
      "sequence_number": 1,
      "question_id": 5125,
      "global_question_id": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1431,
      "audio_id": 8179,
      "text": "I mean, obviously a minimum wage is supposed to be something that covers a broad population, which is really unfair because certain neighborhoods are more expensive to live in than others.",
      "duration": 15.239999771118164,
      "start_time": 9.0,
      "end_time": 24.239999771118164,
      "sequence_number": 2,
      "question_id": 5125,
      "global_question_id": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1432,
      "audio_id": 8179,
      "text": "And rent, for example, is a big part of everyone's budget.",
      "duration": 5.0,
      "start_time": 24.239999771118164,
      "end_time": 29.239999771118164,
      "sequence_number": 3,
      "question_id": 5125,
      "global_question_id": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1433,
      "audio_id": 8179,
      "text": "So I think the minimum wage for my state is, I think it's $11, which is pathetic, of course, and it's nowhere near enough.",
      "duration": 11.35999870300293,
      "start_time": 29.239999771118164,
      "end_time": 40.599998474121094,
      "sequence_number": 4,
      "question_id": 5125,
      "global_question_id": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1434,
      "audio_id": 8179,
      "text": "I think it is, yeah.",
      "duration": 3.200000762939453,
      "start_time": 40.599998474121094,
      "end_time": 43.79999923706055,
      "sequence_number": 5,
      "question_id": 5125,
      "global_question_id": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1435,
      "audio_id": 8179,
      "text": "So a fair minimum wage would be closer to $20 with the, you know, cost of living being so high.",
      "duration": 11.60000228881836,
      "start_time": 43.79999923706055,
      "end_time": 55.400001525878906,
      "sequence_number": 6,
      "question_id": 5125,
      "global_question_id": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1436,
      "audio_id": 8179,
      "text": "Some people would still struggle at that amount, of course, that it's not going to solve every problem.",
      "duration": 6.159999847412109,
      "start_time": 55.400001525878906,
      "end_time": 61.560001373291016,
      "sequence_number": 7,
      "question_id": 5125,
      "global_question_id": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1437,
      "audio_id": 8179,
      "text": "But, you know, with all the expenses most people have, you know, car payments, car insurance, or home insurance, and medical premiums they have to pay for medical bills, it's just such a huge myriad of things that require payments.",
      "duration": 17.520000457763672,
      "start_time": 61.560001373291016,
      "end_time": 79.08000183105469,
      "sequence_number": 8,
      "question_id": 5125,
      "global_question_id": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1438,
      "audio_id": 8179,
      "text": "And I think, you know, whoever sets the minimum wage really has no idea of what it's supposed to cover.",
      "duration": 8.159996032714844,
      "start_time": 79.08000183105469,
      "end_time": 87.23999786376953,
      "sequence_number": 9,
      "question_id": 5125,
      "global_question_id": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1439,
      "audio_id": 8179,
      "text": "I mean, it seems to be, you know, someone would have to rent a room, a small room somewhere and just really, really struggle just for day-to-day survival at the minimum wage.",
      "duration": 13.319999694824219,
      "start_time": 87.23999786376953,
      "end_time": 100.55999755859375,
      "sequence_number": 10,
      "question_id": 5125,
      "global_question_id": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1440,
      "audio_id": 8179,
      "text": "So I think closer to $20, and I think it's about $11 in my state, but I'm not sure.",
      "duration": 4.480003356933594,
      "start_time": 100.55999755859375,
      "end_time": 105.04000091552734,
      "sequence_number": 11,
      "question_id": 5125,
      "global_question_id": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1441,
      "audio_id": 8205,
      "text": "I would do what most reasonable people would do is to save for a rainy day because, unfortunately, there are expenses that pop up that people don't necessarily account for.",
      "duration": 14.819999694824219,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 14.819999694824219,
      "sequence_number": 1,
      "question_id": 5144,
      "global_question_id": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1442,
      "audio_id": 8205,
      "text": "For example, car maintenance and repairs.",
      "duration": 3.739999771118164,
      "start_time": 14.819999694824219,
      "end_time": 18.559999465942383,
      "sequence_number": 2,
      "question_id": 5144,
      "global_question_id": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1443,
      "audio_id": 8205,
      "text": "You may need a lot of work done on your vehicle in order to get to work and just to live your life and if something breaks down, that's an unforeseen expense.",
      "duration": 10.960000991821289,
      "start_time": 18.559999465942383,
      "end_time": 29.520000457763672,
      "sequence_number": 3,
      "question_id": 5144,
      "global_question_id": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1444,
      "audio_id": 8205,
      "text": "So that, like most people, when there's some extra money, it's going to definitely be saved so that you can draw from it when you have more expenses that you haven't accounted for.",
      "duration": 15.639999389648438,
      "start_time": 29.520000457763672,
      "end_time": 45.15999984741211,
      "sequence_number": 4,
      "question_id": 5144,
      "global_question_id": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1445,
      "audio_id": 8245,
      "text": "No.",
      "duration": 8.079999923706055,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 8.079999923706055,
      "sequence_number": 1,
      "question_id": 5158,
      "global_question_id": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1446,
      "audio_id": 8245,
      "text": "Well, I do have one specific concern here, is that at $30 an hour, a lot of businesses will send a lot of their work overseas.",
      "duration": 9.039999961853027,
      "start_time": 9.279999732971191,
      "end_time": 18.31999969482422,
      "sequence_number": 2,
      "question_id": 5158,
      "global_question_id": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1447,
      "audio_id": 8245,
      "text": "There'll be a lot more remote employees working out of third world countries, people who will accept pennies on the dollar even to work very hard.",
      "duration": 8.720001220703125,
      "start_time": 18.31999969482422,
      "end_time": 27.040000915527344,
      "sequence_number": 3,
      "question_id": 5158,
      "global_question_id": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1448,
      "audio_id": 8245,
      "text": "And that's what's happening already though.",
      "duration": 8.480001449584961,
      "start_time": 27.600000381469727,
      "end_time": 36.08000183105469,
      "sequence_number": 4,
      "question_id": 5158,
      "global_question_id": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1449,
      "audio_id": 8245,
      "text": "I think it would be great to help people survive really in a tough economy.",
      "duration": 8.560001373291016,
      "start_time": 37.279998779296875,
      "end_time": 45.84000015258789,
      "sequence_number": 5,
      "question_id": 5158,
      "global_question_id": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1450,
      "audio_id": 8245,
      "text": "However, I don't think that a lot of businesses are going to agree to pay that much. So what's going to happen is a lot of things will be automated.",
      "duration": 5.279998779296875,
      "start_time": 47.68000030517578,
      "end_time": 52.959999084472656,
      "sequence_number": 6,
      "question_id": 5158,
      "global_question_id": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1451,
      "audio_id": 8245,
      "text": "People, companies will invest in robots and kiosks and AI will be taking orders for stuff.",
      "duration": 9.759998321533203,
      "start_time": 53.68000030517578,
      "end_time": 63.439998626708984,
      "sequence_number": 7,
      "question_id": 5158,
      "global_question_id": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1452,
      "audio_id": 8245,
      "text": "It'll replace staff in different places, hotels and restaurants.",
      "duration": 7.519996643066406,
      "start_time": 64.0,
      "end_time": 71.5199966430664,
      "sequence_number": 8,
      "question_id": 5158,
      "global_question_id": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1453,
      "audio_id": 8245,
      "text": "And so what's going to happen is that my concern is that at a minimum wage of $30, a lot of people, a lot of companies specifically, will outsource their labor force and it'll leave a lot of people out of work, which will be a much greater problem.",
      "duration": 21.280006408691406,
      "start_time": 71.5199966430664,
      "end_time": 92.80000305175781,
      "sequence_number": 9,
      "question_id": 5158,
      "global_question_id": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1454,
      "audio_id": 8258,
      "text": "Okay, you aren't specific with regards to where I've experienced discrimination.",
      "duration": 5.400000095367432,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 5.400000095367432,
      "sequence_number": 1,
      "question_id": 5180,
      "global_question_id": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1455,
      "audio_id": 8258,
      "text": "Are we still discussing the workplace?",
      "duration": 3.3799996376037598,
      "start_time": 5.400000095367432,
      "end_time": 8.779999732971191,
      "sequence_number": 2,
      "question_id": 5180,
      "global_question_id": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1456,
      "audio_id": 8258,
      "text": "And are you asking me, have I experienced discrimination in the workplace?",
      "duration": 5.40000057220459,
      "start_time": 8.779999732971191,
      "end_time": 14.180000305175781,
      "sequence_number": 3,
      "question_id": 5180,
      "global_question_id": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1457,
      "audio_id": 8258,
      "text": "Or just in general, let's say walking down the street, walking in the park, that kind of thing.",
      "duration": 5.739999771118164,
      "start_time": 14.180000305175781,
      "end_time": 19.920000076293945,
      "sequence_number": 4,
      "question_id": 5180,
      "global_question_id": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1458,
      "audio_id": 8258,
      "text": "Which of the two did you mean?",
      "duration": 1.2000007629394531,
      "start_time": 19.920000076293945,
      "end_time": 21.1200008392334,
      "sequence_number": 5,
      "question_id": 5180,
      "global_question_id": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1459,
      "audio_id": 8307,
      "text": "Well sure.",
      "duration": 8.380000114440918,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 8.380000114440918,
      "sequence_number": 1,
      "question_id": 5180,
      "global_question_id": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1460,
      "audio_id": 8307,
      "text": "I've gone into, say for example, a barbershop that I was not aware was frequented by white supremacists and they refused to cut my hair, of course.",
      "duration": 5.5,
      "start_time": 8.380000114440918,
      "end_time": 13.880000114440918,
      "sequence_number": 2,
      "question_id": 5180,
      "global_question_id": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1461,
      "audio_id": 8307,
      "text": "I wasn't gonna get my hair cut there anyway because I'm not going to support a racist establishment.",
      "duration": 5.880000114440918,
      "start_time": 13.880000114440918,
      "end_time": 19.760000228881836,
      "sequence_number": 3,
      "question_id": 5180,
      "global_question_id": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1462,
      "audio_id": 8307,
      "text": "But when I arrived there I didn't know that.",
      "duration": 8.319999694824219,
      "start_time": 19.760000228881836,
      "end_time": 28.079999923706055,
      "sequence_number": 4,
      "question_id": 5180,
      "global_question_id": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1463,
      "audio_id": 8307,
      "text": "Once I found out that they were discussing who would take care of me, I guess, because I was ethnic looking and I felt very uncomfortable.",
      "duration": 12.239999771118164,
      "start_time": 28.079999923706055,
      "end_time": 40.31999969482422,
      "sequence_number": 5,
      "question_id": 5180,
      "global_question_id": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1464,
      "audio_id": 8307,
      "text": "And then I heard overt racist statements being made in the barbershop. And so I left.",
      "duration": 8.279998779296875,
      "start_time": 40.31999969482422,
      "end_time": 48.599998474121094,
      "sequence_number": 6,
      "question_id": 5180,
      "global_question_id": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1465,
      "audio_id": 8307,
      "text": "That would be an example of discrimination that I experienced.",
      "duration": 8.480003356933594,
      "start_time": 48.599998474121094,
      "end_time": 57.08000183105469,
      "sequence_number": 7,
      "question_id": 5180,
      "global_question_id": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1466,
      "audio_id": 8410,
      "text": "Well I think people should be hired and promoted, et cetera, based on the merit policy, a meritocracy.",
      "duration": 11.359999656677246,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 11.359999656677246,
      "sequence_number": 1,
      "question_id": 5233,
      "global_question_id": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1467,
      "audio_id": 8410,
      "text": "So I think that it should be up to whoever puts the effort in and is qualified for the position.",
      "duration": 8.40000057220459,
      "start_time": 11.359999656677246,
      "end_time": 19.760000228881836,
      "sequence_number": 2,
      "question_id": 5233,
      "global_question_id": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1468,
      "audio_id": 8410,
      "text": "So I would prefer that someone hired me because they felt I was suitable for the position rather than my race or gender.",
      "duration": 10.039999008178711,
      "start_time": 19.760000228881836,
      "end_time": 29.799999237060547,
      "sequence_number": 3,
      "question_id": 5233,
      "global_question_id": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1469,
      "audio_id": 8410,
      "text": "So I would feel kind of let down, even if it worked in my favor.",
      "duration": 4.520000457763672,
      "start_time": 29.799999237060547,
      "end_time": 34.31999969482422,
      "sequence_number": 4,
      "question_id": 5233,
      "global_question_id": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1470,
      "audio_id": 8410,
      "text": "Even if they were hiring people of my ethnicity to meet a quota, I would feel that my accomplishment would be diminished because I wasn't being hired because I was the best suited for the job.",
      "duration": 15.84000015258789,
      "start_time": 34.31999969482422,
      "end_time": 50.15999984741211,
      "sequence_number": 5,
      "question_id": 5233,
      "global_question_id": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1471,
      "audio_id": 8410,
      "text": "Instead, it was something that the company felt pressured into hiring more minorities.",
      "duration": 7.119998931884766,
      "start_time": 50.15999984741211,
      "end_time": 57.279998779296875,
      "sequence_number": 6,
      "question_id": 5233,
      "global_question_id": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1472,
      "audio_id": 8410,
      "text": "So I would feel kind of bad.",
      "duration": 1.8000030517578125,
      "start_time": 57.279998779296875,
      "end_time": 59.08000183105469,
      "sequence_number": 7,
      "question_id": 5233,
      "global_question_id": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1473,
      "audio_id": 8487,
      "text": "No, I don't think that it's going to be effective.",
      "duration": 7.440000057220459,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 7.440000057220459,
      "sequence_number": 1,
      "question_id": 5300,
      "global_question_id": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1474,
      "audio_id": 8487,
      "text": "I think that if you make gender equality an issue and you hire based on gender, then you have to discriminate against, you know, those who are not minorities.",
      "duration": 5.520000457763672,
      "start_time": 9.119999885559082,
      "end_time": 14.640000343322754,
      "sequence_number": 2,
      "question_id": 5300,
      "global_question_id": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1475,
      "audio_id": 8487,
      "text": "So it doesn't, it creates inequality, you know, even though you have good intentions, because you're intentionally hiring on the basis of the color of someone's skin or their gender rather than whether they're qualified or not.",
      "duration": 22.880000114440918,
      "start_time": 15.4399995803833,
      "end_time": 38.31999969482422,
      "sequence_number": 3,
      "question_id": 5300,
      "global_question_id": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1476,
      "audio_id": 8487,
      "text": "And so this means you're also excluding those who have, or might have been more appropriate for the position based on the color of their skin, because they're not a minority and, and so I, I don't think this is going to be effective.",
      "duration": 7.600002288818359,
      "start_time": 39.119998931884766,
      "end_time": 46.720001220703125,
      "sequence_number": 4,
      "question_id": 5300,
      "global_question_id": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1477,
      "audio_id": 8487,
      "text": "In fact, I see a lot of pushback on the news and in a lot of forums, people are kind of tired of, you know, this virtue signaling that a lot of companies are doing.",
      "duration": 25.040000915527344,
      "start_time": 46.720001220703125,
      "end_time": 71.76000213623047,
      "sequence_number": 5,
      "question_id": 5300,
      "global_question_id": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1478,
      "audio_id": 8529,
      "text": "Sure. I mean, I've worked with a lot of people from a lot of different countries.",
      "duration": 4.039999961853027,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 4.039999961853027,
      "sequence_number": 1,
      "question_id": 5336,
      "global_question_id": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1479,
      "audio_id": 8529,
      "text": "I guess I'll just pick one instance.",
      "duration": 6.939999580383301,
      "start_time": 4.039999961853027,
      "end_time": 10.979999542236328,
      "sequence_number": 2,
      "question_id": 5336,
      "global_question_id": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1480,
      "audio_id": 8529,
      "text": "I at one point worked many years ago for an advertising agency and I worked with someone from Great Britain and yeah, it was great.",
      "duration": 9.220001220703125,
      "start_time": 10.979999542236328,
      "end_time": 20.200000762939453,
      "sequence_number": 3,
      "question_id": 5336,
      "global_question_id": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1481,
      "audio_id": 8529,
      "text": "I had a very charming, entertaining person and I enjoyed their company and we worked well together.",
      "duration": 5.239999771118164,
      "start_time": 20.200000762939453,
      "end_time": 25.440000534057617,
      "sequence_number": 4,
      "question_id": 5336,
      "global_question_id": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1482,
      "audio_id": 8529,
      "text": "It was a very positive experience.",
      "duration": 1.3199996948242188,
      "start_time": 25.440000534057617,
      "end_time": 26.760000228881836,
      "sequence_number": 5,
      "question_id": 5336,
      "global_question_id": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1483,
      "audio_id": 8631,
      "text": "No, I've never, no, I've never heard even discussions about issues with immigration or anyone getting deported. It's not an issue.",
      "duration": 8.15999984741211,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 8.15999984741211,
      "sequence_number": 1,
      "question_id": 5357,
      "global_question_id": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1484,
      "audio_id": 8631,
      "text": "So, typically, with regards to immigration, I mean, the people that I've worked with that were immigrants were legal immigrants, meaning that they had the appropriate documentation, you know, in place, filed away.",
      "duration": 18.0,
      "start_time": 9.520000457763672,
      "end_time": 27.520000457763672,
      "sequence_number": 2,
      "question_id": 5357,
      "global_question_id": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1485,
      "audio_id": 8631,
      "text": "And so there was never any issue because there were never any legal issues.",
      "duration": 6.160001754760742,
      "start_time": 28.399999618530273,
      "end_time": 34.560001373291016,
      "sequence_number": 3,
      "question_id": 5357,
      "global_question_id": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1486,
      "audio_id": 8631,
      "text": "If you, you know, you have your documentation in order, then there's no impact.",
      "duration": 6.879997253417969,
      "start_time": 34.560001373291016,
      "end_time": 41.439998626708984,
      "sequence_number": 4,
      "question_id": 5357,
      "global_question_id": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1487,
      "audio_id": 8631,
      "text": "It's only, you know, illegal immigration that would be, you know, a problem at work or anywhere else, really.",
      "duration": 5.680000305175781,
      "start_time": 42.15999984741211,
      "end_time": 47.84000015258789,
      "sequence_number": 5,
      "question_id": 5357,
      "global_question_id": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1488,
      "audio_id": 8717,
      "text": "Um, no, I think if someone's qualified, then it really shouldn't matter.",
      "duration": 6.300000190734863,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 6.300000190734863,
      "sequence_number": 1,
      "question_id": 5415,
      "global_question_id": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1489,
      "audio_id": 8717,
      "text": "I think it's, you know, um, companies are free to hire whoever they want to.",
      "duration": 4.980000019073486,
      "start_time": 6.320000171661377,
      "end_time": 11.300000190734863,
      "sequence_number": 2,
      "question_id": 5415,
      "global_question_id": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1490,
      "audio_id": 8717,
      "text": "It's, um, they're, they're, uh, going to very likely want to hire someone who is going to perform well for them.",
      "duration": 8.679999351501465,
      "start_time": 11.300000190734863,
      "end_time": 19.979999542236328,
      "sequence_number": 3,
      "question_id": 5415,
      "global_question_id": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1491,
      "audio_id": 8717,
      "text": "Uh, and that's reasonable.",
      "duration": 1.6000003814697266,
      "start_time": 20.81999969482422,
      "end_time": 22.420000076293945,
      "sequence_number": 4,
      "question_id": 5415,
      "global_question_id": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1492,
      "audio_id": 8717,
      "text": "Um, now someone who is qualified has already, uh, established themselves as a viable candidate and so, yeah, no, it's, I think that, um, It's up to the, you know, the, the hiring staff and the hiring department, the human resources of whoever does the hiring at the company to, to make that call.",
      "duration": 24.700000762939453,
      "start_time": 22.520000457763672,
      "end_time": 47.220001220703125,
      "sequence_number": 5,
      "question_id": 5415,
      "global_question_id": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1493,
      "audio_id": 8717,
      "text": "I think, um, it shouldn't matter at all.",
      "duration": 3.05999755859375,
      "start_time": 47.220001220703125,
      "end_time": 50.279998779296875,
      "sequence_number": 6,
      "question_id": 5415,
      "global_question_id": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1494,
      "audio_id": 8818,
      "text": "I think it can be a suggestion.",
      "duration": 7.920000076293945,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 7.920000076293945,
      "sequence_number": 1,
      "question_id": 5459,
      "global_question_id": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1495,
      "audio_id": 8818,
      "text": "I don't think that it's wise to try to force companies, I don't think there should be legislature that demand that companies hire a specific number of local applicants. However, I do think that it's better for the U.S. economy.",
      "duration": 8.399999618530273,
      "start_time": 7.920000076293945,
      "end_time": 16.31999969482422,
      "sequence_number": 2,
      "question_id": 5459,
      "global_question_id": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1496,
      "audio_id": 8818,
      "text": "I think it's better in general for the communities where the employment of a local applicant will make a difference.",
      "duration": 6.720001220703125,
      "start_time": 16.31999969482422,
      "end_time": 23.040000915527344,
      "sequence_number": 3,
      "question_id": 5459,
      "global_question_id": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1497,
      "audio_id": 8818,
      "text": "So I think that it's important for them to consider local applicants, but ultimately I do think it's up to the company's hiring staff and whoever they feel is best qualified for the position.",
      "duration": 9.119998931884766,
      "start_time": 23.040000915527344,
      "end_time": 32.15999984741211,
      "sequence_number": 4,
      "question_id": 5459,
      "global_question_id": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_id": 1498,
      "audio_id": 8818,
      "text": "So I feel that they should have the freedom to hire whoever they feel is best suited for the job.",
      "duration": 32.560001373291016,
      "start_time": 32.15999984741211,
      "end_time": 64.72000122070312,
      "sequence_number": 5,
      "question_id": 5459,
      "global_question_id": 27
    }
  ]
}